article.headline: Princeton 63, Dartmouth 60
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Scott Greenman scored 22 points and made two clutch free throws in the final seconds to lead Princeton to a 63-60 win over Dartmouth Friday night. Edwin Buffmire came up with three key plays down the stretch for Princeton (9-14, 7-3 Ivy League), which defeated the Big Green (5-19, 3-8) for the 19th straight time at Jadwin Gym. Trailing 57-51, Princeton got a layup from Justin Conway and a 3-pointer from Luke Owings to cut the deficit to 57-56. Buffmire's pressure then forced Mike Lang into a turnover, giving the Tigers possession with 51.7 seconds left. At the other end, Buffmire took a pass on the low post, spun into the lane and threw up a left-handed half hook shot that went in. He was fouled on the play and converted the free throw to make it 59-57 with 33.9 remaining. After a timeout, the Big Green worked the ball to Leon Pattman, whose jumper was blocked by Buffmire. Luke Owings got the rebound, was fouled and hit both free throws to make it 61-57 with 9.3 left. Lang hit a 3-pointer to pull Dartmouth back within one, but Greenman's foul shots with 3.6 seconds left wrapped up the win for the Tigers. Owings and Justin Conway each had 17 points for Princeton. Lang had 12 points, while Dan Biber and Pattman had nine each for Dartmouth.
